{"questionId":"15261","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Sila High School has 110 students. They each take exactly one language class from a choice of English, Spanish or Chinese. The following table shows the number of female and male students in the three different language classes.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/5ff71a6b883c55d36f76d26c25b205cad91d8092.png\"></p>\n<p>A <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\chi ^2}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>χ</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;test was carried out at the 5 % significance level to analyse the relationship between gender and student choice of language class.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The critical value at the 5 % significance level for this test is 5.99.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>One student is chosen at random from this school.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Another student is chosen at random from this school.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the probability that neither of the two students take the Spanish class.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{88}}{{110}} \\times \\frac{{87}}{{109}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>88</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>110</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>87</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>109</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(M1)</em></strong><strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <strong><em>(M1)</em></strong> for multiplying two fractions. Award <strong><em>(M1)</em></strong> for multiplying their correct fractions.</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {\\frac{{46}}{{110}}} \\right)\\left( {\\frac{{45}}{{109}}} \\right) + 2\\left( {\\frac{{46}}{{110}}} \\right)\\left( {\\frac{{42}}{{109}}} \\right) + \\left( {\\frac{{42}}{{110}}} \\right)\\left( {\\frac{{41}}{{109}}} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>46</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>110</mn>\n        </mrow>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>45</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>109</mn>\n        </mrow>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>46</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>110</mn>\n        </mrow>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>42</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>109</mn>\n        </mrow>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>42</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>110</mn>\n        </mrow>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>41</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>109</mn>\n        </mrow>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(M1)</em></strong><strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <strong><em>(M1)</em></strong> for correct products; <strong><em>(M1)</em></strong> for adding 4 products.</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"0.639\\,\\,\\,\\left( {0.638532 \\ldots {\\text{,}}